defs.docs:
A library for finding occurrences of many patterns at once. This library
provides multiple pattern search principally through an implementation of the
[Aho-Corasick algorithm](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aho%E2%80%93Corasick_algorithm),
which builds a fast finite state machine for executing searches in linear time.

defs.name: AhoCorasick
defs.docs: An automaton for searching multiple strings in linear time.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new Aho-Corasick automaton using the default configuration.

defs.name: new_auto_configured
defs.docs:
Build an Aho-Corasick automaton with an automatically determined
 configuration.

defs.name: is_match
defs.docs:
Returns true if and only if this automaton matches the haystack at any
 position.

defs.name: earliest_find
defs.docs: Returns the location of the first detected match in `haystack`.

defs.name: find
defs.docs:
Returns the location of the first match according to the match
 semantics that this automaton was constructed with.

defs.name: find_iter
defs.value: fn <'a, 'b, B> (&'a self, haystack: &'b B) -> FindIter<'a, 'b, S>
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator of non-overlapping matches, using the match
 semantics that this automaton was constructed with.

defs.name: find_overlapping_iter
defs.value: fn <'a, 'b, B> (&'a self, haystack: &'b B) -> FindOverlappingIter<'a, 'b, S>
defs.docs: Returns an iterator of overlapping matches in the given `haystack`.

defs.name: replace_all
defs.docs:
Replace all matches with a corresponding value in the `replace_with`
 slice given. Matches correspond to the same matches as reported by
 [`find_iter`](struct.AhoCorasick.html#method.find_iter).

defs.name: replace_all_bytes
defs.docs:
Replace all matches using raw bytes with a corresponding value in the
 `replace_with` slice given. Matches correspond to the same matches as
 reported by [`find_iter`](struct.AhoCorasick.html#method.find_iter).

defs.name: replace_all_with
defs.value: fn <F> (&self, haystack: &str, dst: &mut String, mut replace_with: F) -> ()
defs.docs:
Replace all matches using a closure called on each match.
 Matches correspond to the same matches as reported by
 [`find_iter`](struct.AhoCorasick.html#method.find_iter).

defs.name: replace_all_with_bytes
defs.value: fn <F> (&self, haystack: &[u8], dst: &mut Vec<u8>, mut replace_with: F) -> ()
defs.docs:
Replace all matches using raw bytes with a closure called on each
 match. Matches correspond to the same matches as reported by
 [`find_iter`](struct.AhoCorasick.html#method.find_iter).

defs.name: stream_find_iter
defs.value: fn <'a, R> (&'a self, rdr: R) -> StreamFindIter<'a, R, S>
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator of non-overlapping matches in the given
 stream. Matches correspond to the same matches as reported by
 [`find_iter`](struct.AhoCorasick.html#method.find_iter).

defs.name: stream_replace_all
defs.value: fn <R, W, B> (&self, rdr: R, wtr: W, replace_with: &[B]) -> io::Result<()>
defs.docs:
Search for and replace all matches of this automaton in
 the given reader, and write the replacements to the given
 writer. Matches correspond to the same matches as reported by
 [`find_iter`](struct.AhoCorasick.html#method.find_iter).

defs.name: stream_replace_all_with
defs.value: fn <R, W, F> (&self, rdr: R, mut wtr: W, mut replace_with: F) -> io::Result<()>
defs.docs:
Search the given reader and replace all matches of this automaton
 using the given closure. The result is written to the given
 writer. Matches correspond to the same matches as reported by
 [`find_iter`](struct.AhoCorasick.html#method.find_iter).

defs.name: match_kind
defs.docs: Returns the match kind used by this automaton.

defs.name: max_pattern_len
defs.docs: Returns the length of the longest pattern matched by this automaton.

defs.name: pattern_count
defs.docs: Return the total number of patterns matched by this automaton.

defs.name: supports_overlapping
defs.docs:
Returns true if and only if this automaton supports reporting
 overlapping matches.

defs.name: supports_stream
defs.docs: Returns true if and only if this automaton supports stream searching.

defs.name: heap_bytes
defs.docs:
Returns the approximate total amount of heap used by this automaton, in
 units of bytes.

defs.name: FindIter
defs.docs: An iterator of non-overlapping matches in a particular haystack.

defs.name: FindOverlappingIter
defs.docs: An iterator of overlapping matches in a particular haystack.

defs.name: StreamFindIter
defs.docs: An iterator that reports Aho-Corasick matches in a stream.

defs.name: AhoCorasickBuilder
defs.docs: A builder for configuring an Aho-Corasick automaton.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new builder for configuring an Aho-Corasick automaton.

defs.name: build
defs.docs:
Build an Aho-Corasick automaton using the configuration set on this
 builder.

defs.name: build_with_size
defs.value: fn <S, I, P> (&self, patterns: I) -> Result<AhoCorasick<S>>
defs.docs:
Build an Aho-Corasick automaton using the configuration set on this
 builder with a specific state identifier representation. This only has
 an effect when the `dfa` option is enabled.

defs.name: auto_configure
defs.docs:
Automatically configure the settings on this builder according to the
 patterns that will be used to construct the automaton.

defs.name: match_kind
defs.docs: Set the desired match semantics.

defs.name: anchored
defs.docs:
Enable anchored mode, which requires all matches to start at the
 first position in a haystack.

defs.name: ascii_case_insensitive
defs.docs: Enable ASCII-aware case insensitive matching.

defs.name: dense_depth
defs.docs:
Set the limit on how many NFA states use a dense representation for
 their transitions.

defs.name: dfa
defs.docs:
Compile the standard Aho-Corasick automaton into a deterministic finite
 automaton (DFA).

defs.name: prefilter
defs.docs: Enable heuristic prefilter optimizations.

defs.name: byte_classes
defs.docs:
Shrink the size of the transition alphabet by mapping bytes to their
 equivalence classes. This only has an effect when the `dfa` option is
 enabled.

defs.name: premultiply
defs.docs:
Premultiply state identifiers in the transition table. This only has
 an effect when the `dfa` option is enabled.

defs.name: Standard
defs.docs:
Use standard match semantics, which support overlapping matches. When
 used with non-overlapping matches, matches are reported as they are
 seen.

defs.name: LeftmostFirst
defs.docs:
Use leftmost-first match semantics, which reports leftmost matches.
 When there are multiple possible leftmost matches, the match
 corresponding to the pattern that appeared earlier when constructing
 the automaton is reported.

defs.name: LeftmostLongest
defs.docs:
Use leftmost-longest match semantics, which reports leftmost matches.
 When there are multiple possible leftmost matches, the longest match
 is chosen.

defs.name: __Nonexhaustive
defs.docs: Hints that destructuring should not be exhaustive.

defs.name: MatchKind
defs.docs: A knob for controlling the match semantics of an Aho-Corasick automaton.

defs.name: ID
defs.docs: The representation used for state identifiers in this automaton.

defs.name: Error
defs.docs:
An error that occurred during the construction of an Aho-Corasick
 automaton.

defs.name: StateIDOverflow
defs.docs:
An error that occurs when constructing an automaton would require the
 use of a state ID that overflows the chosen state ID representation.
 For example, if one is using `u8` for state IDs and builds a DFA with
 257 states, then the last state's ID will be `256` which cannot be
 represented with `u8`.

defs.name: PremultiplyOverflow
defs.docs:
An error that occurs when premultiplication of state IDs is requested
 when constructing an Aho-Corasick DFA, but doing so would overflow the
 chosen state ID representation.

defs.name: ErrorKind
defs.docs: The kind of error that occurred.

defs.name: kind
defs.docs: Return the kind of this error.

defs.name: packed
defs.docs:
A lower level API for packed multiple substring search, principally for a small
number of patterns.

defs.name: LeftmostFirst
defs.docs:
Use leftmost-first match semantics, which reports leftmost matches.
 When there are multiple possible leftmost matches, the match
 corresponding to the pattern that appeared earlier when constructing
 the automaton is reported.

defs.name: LeftmostLongest
defs.docs:
Use leftmost-longest match semantics, which reports leftmost matches.
 When there are multiple possible leftmost matches, the longest match
 is chosen.

defs.name: __Nonexhaustive
defs.docs: Hints that destructuring should not be exhaustive.

defs.name: MatchKind
defs.docs:
A knob for controlling the match semantics of a packed multiple string
 searcher.

defs.name: Config
defs.docs: The configuration for a packed multiple pattern searcher.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Create a new default configuration. A default configuration uses
 leftmost-first match semantics.

defs.name: builder
defs.docs:
Create a packed builder from this configuration. The builder can be
 used to accumulate patterns and create a
 [`Searcher`](struct.Searcher.html)
 from them.

defs.name: match_kind
defs.docs: Set the match semantics for this configuration.

defs.name: force_teddy
defs.docs: An undocumented method for forcing the use of the Teddy algorithm.

defs.name: force_teddy_fat
defs.docs: An undocumented method for forcing the use of the Fat Teddy algorithm.

defs.name: force_avx
defs.docs:
An undocumented method for forcing the use of SSE (`Some(false)`) or
 AVX (`Some(true)`) algorithms.

defs.name: force_rabin_karp
defs.docs: An undocumented method for forcing the use of the Rabin-Karp algorithm.

defs.name: Builder
defs.docs: A builder for constructing a packed searcher from a collection of patterns.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Create a new builder for constructing a multi-pattern searcher. This
 constructor uses the default configuration.

defs.name: build
defs.docs: Build a searcher from the patterns added to this builder so far.

defs.name: add
defs.docs: Add the given pattern to this set to match.

defs.name: extend
defs.value: fn <I, P> (&mut self, patterns: I) -> &mut Builder
defs.docs: Add the given iterator of patterns to this set to match.

defs.name: Searcher
defs.docs: A packed searcher for quickly finding occurrences of multiple patterns.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
A convenience function for constructing a searcher from an iterator
 of things that can be converted to a `&[u8]`.

defs.name: find
defs.docs:
Return the first occurrence of any of the patterns in this searcher,
 according to its match semantics, in the given haystack. The `Match`
 returned will include the identifier of the pattern that matched, which
 corresponds to the index of the pattern (starting from `0`) in which it
 was added.

defs.name: find_at
defs.value: fn <B> (&self, haystack: B, at: usize) -> Option<Match>
defs.docs:
Return the first occurrence of any of the patterns in this searcher,
 according to its match semantics, in the given haystack starting from
 the given position.

defs.name: find_iter
defs.value: fn <'a, 'b, B> (&'a self, haystack: &'b B) -> FindIter<'a, 'b>
defs.docs:
Return an iterator of non-overlapping occurrences of the patterns in
 this searcher, according to its match semantics, in the given haystack.

defs.name: match_kind
defs.docs: Returns the match kind used by this packed searcher.

defs.name: minimum_len
defs.docs:
Returns the minimum length of a haystack that is required in order for
 packed searching to be effective.

defs.name: heap_bytes
defs.docs:
Returns the approximate total amount of heap used by this searcher, in
 units of bytes.

defs.name: FindIter
defs.docs: An iterator over non-overlapping matches from a packed searcher.

defs.name: Sealed
defs.docs:
Sealed stops crates other than aho-corasick from implementing any
 traits that use it.

defs.name: StateID
defs.value:
StateID: private::Sealed + Clone + Copy + Debug + Eq + Hash + PartialEq + PartialOrd +
Ord
defs.docs: A trait describing the representation of an automaton's state identifier.

defs.name: from_usize
defs.docs: Convert from a `usize` to this implementation's representation.

defs.name: to_usize
defs.docs: Convert this implementation's representation to a `usize`.

defs.name: max_id
defs.docs: Return the maximum state identifier supported by this representation.

defs.name: Match
defs.docs: A representation of a match reported by an Aho-Corasick automaton.

defs.name: pattern
defs.docs: Returns the identifier of the pattern that matched.

defs.name: start
defs.docs: The starting position of the match.

defs.name: end
defs.docs: The ending position of the match.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs:
Returns true if and only if this match is empty. That is, when
 `start() == end()`.
